The data controllers have defined a contact point for data subjects which facilitates the fulfilment
of the data subject rights according to Article 26 (1) sentence 3 of the GDPR for the users and the
data controllers. This common point of contact is the above-mentioned MindDoc Health.
Designation of the processing
Collection, storage, modification, viewing, deletion and use of personal
data in the context of online psychotherapy and related initiation activities (e.g. initial interview, catamneses)
Purpose of the processing
For MindDoc Healthcare, the purpose of the processing is the fulfilment and implementation of the contractual relationships
with (future) patients of online psychotherapy.MindDoc Health processes personal data- for the purpose of operating
the applications for the implementation of online psychotherapy of data security,- for internal administrative purposes,
e.g. in order to avoid duplications by comparing the data with already existing data and thus to comply with the principle
of data economy, and to ensure central patient management and optimal care across different treatment intensities.
If you have any questions about our data protection measures, the processing of your data or the protection of your rights
